description: Customer information including identification and location details
business_definition: A customer is an organization or individual that purchases or uses our products and services
The unique code assigned to identify each customer in our system
The official registered name of the customer organization or individual

description: Country where the customer is located
business_definition: The country in which the customer's primary business location is registered
A machine is a piece of manufacturing equipment owned by a customer and tracked in our system
The unique serial number assigned to identify each machine unit
The customer organization that owns and operates the machine

description: Category or type of the machine
business_definition: The classification of the machine based on its technology and capabilities (AT/NXT/NXE)

description: Specific model designation of the machine
business_definition: The manufacturer's model number identifying the specific machine configuration
A location represents a physical site where a customer operates and where machines may be installed
The unique code assigned to identify each physical location or site
The customer who operates or owns the location

description: Name of the site or location
business_definition: The business name or designation of the physical location

description: City where the location is situated
business_definition: The city in which the physical site is located

description: Country where the location is situated
business_definition: The country in which the physical site is located
The latitude coordinate for precise geographic positioning of the site
The longitude coordinate for precise geographic positioning of the site
Install base represents the deployment of a specific machine at a customer location with installation details
The specific machine unit that has been deployed at a location
The physical site where the machine has been deployed
The date when the machine was commissioned and became operational at the location
A state represents the operational status of a machine during a specific time period (productive idle etc)

description: Unique identifier for each state record
business_definition: The unique code assigned to identify each state transition record
The machine that is experiencing this operational state
The standardized code identifying the type of operational state (1-P for Productive 3-Idle for Idle)
The descriptive label for the operational state
The timestamp when the machine entered this operational state
The timestamp when the machine exited this operational state
An event log captures specific operational events that occur during machine operation
The unique code assigned to identify each event record
The machine on which the event occurred
The timestamp when the event was recorded
The classification of the event (lot_started lot_completed etc)
The numeric measurement or metric captured during the event
